      "title": "On the uniqueness of limit cycles surrounding one or more singularities for Liénard equations",
      "abstract": "In this paper we prove a theorem on the uniqueness of limit cycles surrounding one or more singularities for Li?nard equations. By using this theorem we give a positive answer to the conjecture in Dumortier and Rousseau (1990 Nonlinearity 3 1015 - 39), completing the classification of the cubic Li?nard equations with linear damping. It also finishes the study of the generic three-parameter unfoldings of the nilpotent focus in the plane."
